Class EntryIteratorPopulatedTests

java.lang.Object
myTest.EntryIteratorPopulatedTests
public class EntryIteratorPopulatedTests extends Object
Tests the functionality for an EntryIterator linked to a populated map. This class contains tests for the EntryIterator methods for which the populated state of the map is relevant.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
  • MapAdapter.EntryIterator
  • MapAdapter.EntrySet
  • MapAdapter.Entry
Design
This test class is designed to ensure that the EntryIterator and Entry class methods work correctly when the map is populated.
Libraries
JUnit 4.13, Hamcrest 1.3

  • Method Details

    • setUp

      public void setUp()
      Sets up the test environment by initializing a MapAdapter instance, populating it with 100 entries in using "key"+i as key and "value"+(i % 50) as value to ensure coverage of edge cases involving duplicate values. After creating the MapAdapter, an EntrySet instance is created obtaining its entry set view. After that, an EntryIterator instance is created from the obtained EntrySet.

    • testStartToFinish

      public void testStartToFinish()
      Tests iterator capability to iterate from start to finish.
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the EntryIterator can iterate through all entries in the map from start to finish. Ensuring that both hasNext() and next() methods work correctly in a populated state.
      Description
      The hasNext() is called repeatedly on the iterator created in the setUp() method until it returns false, on each iteration next() is called on the iterator to traverse the entries and a counter is incremented. The test asserts that the counter equals the number of entries in the map, which is 100.
      Preconditions
      The map must be populated with 100 entries before this test runs.
      Postconditions
      The iterator is at the end of the entry set, the map remains unchanged.
      Expected Results
      Iterator traverses all 100 entries in the map without any issues.

    • testRemoveAll

      public void testRemoveAll()
      Tests the remove method of the EntryIterator. It checks that all entries can be removed from the map using the iterator.
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the EntryIterator's remove() method works correctly in a populated state.
      Description
      The hasNext() is called repeatedly until it returns false, while hasNext() returns true, next() is called to traverse the entries asserting that each entry is not null. Successively, the remove() method is called to remove each entry from the map. After the loop, the map is asserted to be empty.
      Preconditions
      The map must be populated with 100 entries before this test runs.
      Postconditions
      The map is empty after all entries are removed. The iterator is at the end of the entry set.
      Expected Results
      The test should pass if the remove method can successfully remove all entries from the map without any issues.

    • testRemoveWithNext

      public void testRemoveWithNext()
      Tests the remove method of the EntryIterator after calling next(). It checks that an entry can be removed after it has been accessed.
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the EntryIterator's remove() method works correctly after calling next().
      Description
      This test calls the MapAdapter.EntryIterator.remove() method using the EntryIterator created in the setUp() method to an entry after calling next(). It asserts that the entry is no longer present in the map.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated and populated with entries.
      Postconditions
      The map does not contain the removed entry after the remove operation.
      Expected Results
      The removed entry's key should not be present in the map.

    • testRemoveWithoutNext

      public void testRemoveWithoutNext()
      Tests the remove method of the EntryIterator without calling next(). It checks that an IllegalStateException is thrown when remove() is called without a preceding call to next().
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the EntryIterator's remove() method throws an IllegalStateException when called without a preceding call to next().
      Description
      This test uses the EntryIterator created in the setUp() method to call remove() without calling next(). It asserts that an IllegalStateException is thrown.
      Preconditions
      The EntryIterator is correctly instantiated.
      Postconditions
      The state of the EntryIterator should remain unchanged after the test.
      Expected Results
      The test should pass if an IllegalStateException is thrown when remove() is called without a preceding call to next().

    • testEntrySetValue

      public void testEntrySetValue()
      Tests the setValue method of the Entry class. It checks that the value of an entry can be updated and that the map reflects this change.
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the Entry class's setValue() method updates the value of an entry and that the map reflects this change correctly.
      Description
      An Entry is obtained from the EntryIterator created in the setUp() method. The setValue() method is called on the Entry instance to update its value. The test asserts that the setValue() method returns the old value and that the map reflects the updated value.
      Preconditions
      The map must be populated with entries before this test runs.
      Postconditions
      The map should reflect the updated value after the setValue() operation.
      Expected Results
      The test should pass if the setValue() method can successfully update the value of an entry and the map reflects this change.

    • testEntryHashCode

      public void testEntryHashCode()
      Tests the hashCode method of the Entry class. It checks that two equal entries have the same hash code.
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the Entry class's hashCode() method works correctly and complies with the contract that equal objects must have equal hash codes.
      Description
      This test obtains an entry from the map, creates another map with an identical entry, and asserts that their hash codes are equal.
      Preconditions
      The map must be populated.
      Postconditions
      The map remains unchanged.
      Expected Results
      Equal entries have the same hash code.
